{
  "stem": "10572.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And Orry Goldberg assured me that someday I could be king in Alkhart but I would be a schnorrer in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I told him that I didn't believe in monarchy anyhow and would-- [LAUGHS]-- give up to be a king in Elkhart.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And wonderfully enough, that when I went in the Army, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Goldberg gave blood to the American Red Cross in my name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went to Chicago, and booked out the passage for my parents, used the $700, and then tried to find a job in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that became very, very difficult for all kinds of reasons that I don't necessarily want to go into.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, there was some social workers at the Jewish Committee on 130 Northwest Street who told me that I was not justified to come to Chicago, that I belonged to Indiana because I had been sent to Indiana.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I told Miss [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Sabbath ?], the granddaughter of Judge [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Sabbath ?], that I was not a piece of luggage that could be shipped back and forth, and I would stay in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then another wonderful thing happened to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I met a newspaperman, Francis Chase, Jr., whose mother had died when he was born.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was brought up by a Jewish neighbor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he took me in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He and his wife practically adopted me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] then about six months later, I got a letter from my father that they had been called to the American consulate in Hamburg, and were asked by the American consul, who was paying for their passage.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father, who always was honest and told the truth, told them that his son, with a loan from Mrs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Hamilton, and the [INAUDIBLE] was paying for the passage.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the vice consul at the Hamburg, consul general, American consul general, an obvious anti-Semite, told them that it was in violation of an immigration law that was passed in 1924, and therefore, he had to refuse their visa, because it was an immigration law that said, whenever organizations pay for your immigration, you become an illegal immigrant.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that dated back to 1924 when the steel and coal industry brought thousands and thousands of East Europeans on ships and in order to protect American labor.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in a misinterpretation of this law, my parents were sentenced to death by Vice Consul Getsinge.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I will not bless his name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father wrote me a letter, and it was a letter that looked to me like his last will.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was his last will.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Told me what to do with my life, and this was it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And Frances Chase-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --hadn't seen me like you would see me today, couple of times, and I broke down.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all my dreams had-- suddenly were wiped away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Chase, being the wonderful short-story writer he was, came up with an unbelievable idea.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had once worked for the Anti-Defamation League for Miles Goldberg as an undercover agent and had interrogated Father Covlin in Michigan as a newspaper man.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he went that night to the telephone and called Miles Goldberg to ask him if he could see him.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Francis Chase and I went to 130 Northwest Street the next day and talked to Miles Goldberg.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Miles Goldberg listened to my story and finally got on the phone and called Senator Barbour, the Republican of New Jersey, to ask him to do him a favor and contact the consul general in Hamburg and guarantee our political liability.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was this go-between that ultimately got the visa for my parents.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they arrived here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My parents and my sister.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember the story that one day while I was living with Frances Chase and Billie Chase, his wife-- we had a big, colored woman was the maid there.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in the morning, just as I was leaving for work, the Western Union man delivered a telegram.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it said, Received visas, happy, secured passage, received visas.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I'd opened the telegram, and I grabbed this lady.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she-- she didn't quite know what had happened to me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was dancing around with her, screaming at things in a languages that she didn't understand.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then afterwards, I went to my newspaper man at Howard Street.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I always bought my newspaper from a little Jewish fellow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I hugged him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he didn't know what had happened to me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I got on the L to go downtown, and people looked at me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They didn't quite know what happened to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I didn't care.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I'd finally made it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "At least I thought I had.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
